urlText: L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line night trackwork
content:
From 7.30pm Monday 30 November to 1am Friday 4 December, nightly from 7.30pm to 1am, light rail services will not run between Circular Quay and Randwick on the L2 Randwick Line, or between Circular Quay and Juniors Kinsgford on the L3 Kingsford Line, due to planned maintenance works.

Each night, use alternative transport in both directions:
  • Trains between Circular Quay and Central Chalmers Street,
  • Replacement buses between Central Chalmers Street and Randwick or Juniors Kingsford. Replacement buses will run every 6 minutes in.
Normal light rail services will resume from 5am Friday 4 December.

Allow extra travel time, use the Trip Planner to check your options or use the nearby replacement bus stop locations.
subtitle: L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line night trackwork

urlText: Trackwork between Glenfield, Sydenham and Central via the Airport
content:
Saturday 5 and Sunday 6 December 
  • Buses replace trains between Glenfield and Sydenham, and between Sydenham and Central via the Airport.
  • Buses to Airport stations stop at Sydenham, Wolli Creek, International Airport, Domestic Airport, Mascot, Green Square and Central only. 
  • T4 Eastern Suburbs & Illawarra Line trains run between Sydenham and Bondi Junction.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between:
    • Macarthur and North Sydney via Granville
    • Campbelltown and Central, platforms 1-12, via Regents Park 
  • Trackwork on the City Circle may also affect how you travel. 
  • If you are travelling to Circular Quay change at Central, Town Hall or Wynyard for the light rail. 
  • On Saturday from 5.30am until 9.30am, trains between Campbelltown and Central run via Granville.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
